      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>Members of the Bolling family acquired land in what is now
         Petersburg early in the 18th century and increased their
         holdings over the years. The record below seems to concern
         property in the area from Sycamore Street (Petersburg, Va.),
         to Lieutenant Run. Robert B. Bolling (1805-1881) was the son
         of Robert Bolling of Centre Hill.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>The volume records charges to individuals and companies for
         the rent of homes, tenements, stores, and shops in Petersburg,
         Virginia. Included are date, account balance or amount in
         arrear, lot number, name of tenant, description of property,
         amount of rent or amount paid, remarks, and date lease
         commenced. It covers the years 1841-1844 and 1850-1855. See
         also Bolling family Papers, 1653-1843 (acc. 20076).</p>
      </scopecontent>
